## Core Development Principles

### 1. Code Quality & Architecture
- Write clean, semantic HTML with proper accessibility attributes
- Use meaningful class names and component structure
- Implement mobile-first responsive design
- Ensure cross-browser compatibility
- Follow modern web standards and best practices

### 2. CSS & Styling Guidelines (Tailwind CSS Expert Integration)

#### CSS Conflict Resolution & Architecture
- **Specificity Management**: Always analyze existing CSS for potential conflicts before adding new styles
- **Cascade Analysis**: Understand inheritance patterns and prevent unintended style overwrites
- **Scoping Strategy**: Implement proper component isolation using CSS modules or Tailwind's layer system
- **Legacy CSS Integration**: Safely integrate Tailwind with existing Bootstrap and custom CSS

#### Before Writing Any CSS
1. **Audit Existing Styles**: Scan project for existing CSS files, frameworks, and potential conflicts
2. **Analyze Component Tree**: Understand parent-child relationships and inheritance patterns
3. **Check Configuration**: Review current styling approach and suggest optimizations
4. **Identify Patterns**: Look for repeated styling patterns that should be abstracted

#### Code Quality Standards
- **Semantic Naming**: Use meaningful class combinations and component names
- **Responsive Design**: Mobile-first approach with proper breakpoint usage
- **Accessibility**: Ensure WCAG compliance with proper contrast, focus states, screen reader support
- **Performance**: Minimize bundle size, avoid unnecessary utilities, optimize for Core Web Vitals

#### Component Architecture Patterns
- **Variant Systems**: Use conditional styling for different states
- **Compound Components**: Build complex UI patterns with proper style isolation
- **Design Tokens**: Abstract colors, spacing, typography into reusable tokens
- **Layer Management**: Proper use of CSS layers for organization

### 3. SEO Optimization Guidelines (SEO Expert Integration)

#### Initial Project Analysis Protocol
Upon working on any file, immediately check for:
- Meta tags implementation and quality
- Google Analytics presence (GA4 or Universal Analytics)
- Structured data (JSON-LD)
- Open Graph tags
- Canonical URLs
- Image optimization status
- Loading performance indicators
- Mobile responsiveness

#### Universal On-Page SEO Requirements

**Meta Tags Template:**
```html
<!-- Primary Meta Tags -->
<title>[Primary Keyword] - [Secondary Keyword] | [Project Name] (50-60 chars)</title>
<meta name="description" content="[Action verb] [benefit]. [Feature/Service]. [Call-to-action]. (150-160 chars)">
<meta name="keywords" content="[Primary Keywords from Project Configuration]">

<!-- Viewport and Technical -->
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<link rel="canonical" href="https://[Domain from Project Configuration]/[page]">

<!-- Indexing Control -->
<meta name="robots" content="index, follow, max-snippet:-1, max-image-preview:large, max-video-preview:-1">
```

**Open Graph & Twitter Cards:**
```html
<!-- Open Graph / Facebook -->
<meta property="og:type" content="website">
<meta property="og:url" content="https://[Domain from Project Configuration]/[page]">
<meta property="og:title" content="[Title from Meta Tags]">
<meta property="og:description" content="[Description from Meta Tags]">
<meta property="og:image" content="https://[Domain from Project Configuration]/og-image.jpg">
<meta property="og:image:width" content="1200">
<meta property="og:image:height" content="630">

<!-- Twitter -->
<meta name="twitter:card" content="summary_large_image">
<meta name="twitter:url" content="https://[Domain from Project Configuration]/[page]">
<meta name="twitter:title" content="[Title from Meta Tags]">
<meta name="twitter:description" content="[Description from Meta Tags]">
<meta name="twitter:image" content="https://[Domain from Project Configuration]/twitter-image.jpg">
```

#### Industry-Specific SEO Optimization
Based on the **Website Type** from Project Configuration:

**Portfolio/Creative:**
- ImageObject schema for portfolio pieces
- Portfolio showcase optimization with proper alt text
- Case study structure with detailed descriptions
- Creative work metadata including techniques and mediums
- Professional bio optimization with relevant keywords

**E-commerce:**
- Product schema markup
- Review/Rating schemas
- Price and availability markup
- Category page optimization
- Faceted navigation handling

**Blog/Publishing:**
- Article schema
- Author markup
- Content freshness signals
- Category/tag optimization
- Related posts structure

**Local Business:**
- LocalBusiness schema
- NAP consistency (Name, Address, Phone)
- Google My Business optimization tips
- Local citation recommendations
- Service area pages

**Corporate/B2B:**
- Organization schema
- Service page optimization
- White paper/resource optimization
- LinkedIn integration suggestions

#### Performance Optimization
**Core Web Vitals Targets (from Project Configuration):**
- **LCP**: < [Configured Value]s
- **FID**: < [Configured Value]ms
- **CLS**: < [Configured Value]
- **TTFB**: < [Configured Value]ms

**Image Optimization Protocol:**
- Use WebP format with JPEG fallback
- Implement responsive images with srcset
- Lazy loading for below-fold images
- Quality 80-85 for photos, 90-95 for graphics
- Descriptive, keyword-relevant alt text
- Descriptive file naming conventions

### 4. Content Optimization Guidelines

#### Universal Content SEO Rules
1. **Title Structure**: Primary Keyword - Secondary | [Project Name]
2. **URL Structure**: /category/descriptive-keyword-slug
3. **Heading Hierarchy**: 
   - One H1 per page (matches search intent)
   - H2s for main sections
   - H3s for subsections
4. **Content Length**: Use targets from Project Configuration
5. **Internal Linking**: 3-5 contextual links per 1000 words

### 5. Google Analytics Integration

#### Quick GA4 Setup Guide
```html
<!-- Google Analytics 4 -->
<script async src="https://www.googletagmanager.com/gtag/js?id=[Google Analytics ID from Project Configuration]"></script>
<script>
  window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
  function gtag(){dataLayer.push(arguments);}
  gtag('js', new Date());
  gtag('config', '[Google Analytics ID from Project Configuration]');
</script>
```

#### Analytics Setup Checklist
1. Verify GA4 property creation
2. Implement basic tracking code
3. Set up conversion events (form submissions, purchases, portfolio views)
4. Enable enhanced measurement (scroll, outbound clicks, site search)
5. Link to Google Search Console
6. Set up custom events for important user interactions

### 6. Technical SEO Foundations

#### Robots.txt Configuration
```
User-agent: *
Allow: /
Disallow: /cgi-bin/
Disallow: /tmp/
Disallow: /private/
Crawl-delay: 1

# Block common development/sensitive paths
Disallow: /api/private/
Disallow: /*.json$
Disallow: /*.xml$ 
Allow: /sitemap.xml

Sitemap: [Sitemap URL from Project Configuration]
```

#### Universal Structured Data Base
```json
{
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "WebSite",
  "url": "https://[Domain from Project Configuration]",
  "name": "[Project Name from Project Configuration]",
  "potentialAction": {
    "@type": "SearchAction",
    "target": "https://[Domain from Project Configuration]/search?q={search_term_string}",
    "query-input": "required name=search_term_string"
  }
}
```

### 7. Problem-Solving Methodology

#### When Styling Components:
1. **Analyze Context**: Understand the component's purpose, parent containers, and usage patterns
2. **Check Inheritance**: Identify inherited styles that might affect the component
3. **Plan Responsive Strategy**: Design mobile-first with logical breakpoint progression
4. **Implement Accessibility**: Include focus states, color contrast, and semantic markup
5. **Test Across Browsers**: Consider browser-specific quirks and fallbacks
6. **Optimize Performance**: Remove unused utilities, combine similar classes

#### When Debugging CSS Issues:
1. **Inspect Specificity**: Use browser dev tools to identify override sources
2. **Check Cascade Order**: Verify CSS import order and layer priorities
3. **Validate Syntax**: Ensure proper class names and combinations
4. **Test Responsive**: Verify behavior across all breakpoints
5. **Cross-browser Validation**: Test in multiple browsers and devices

### 8. Quality Assurance Checklist

Before delivering any solution:
- [ ] No conflicts with existing CSS detected
- [ ] Responsive design tested across all major breakpoints
- [ ] Accessibility compliance verified (contrast, focus states, semantic markup)
- [ ] Performance impact assessed (bundle size, render speed)
- [ ] Cross-browser compatibility confirmed
- [ ] Component reusability considered
- [ ] Code maintainability optimized
- [ ] Design system consistency maintained
- [ ] Mobile-friendly test passes
- [ ] All pages have unique titles and descriptions
- [ ] Images are optimized and have alt text
- [ ] HTTPS is properly implemented
- [ ] Canonical URLs are set correctly

### 9. Communication Style

- **Explain Reasoning**: Always explain why specific approaches were chosen
- **Highlight Conflicts**: Proactively identify and resolve potential issues
- **Suggest Improvements**: Recommend optimizations for existing code
- **Provide Alternatives**: Offer multiple solutions with trade-off explanations
- **Performance Insights**: Include performance implications of choices
- **Best Practices**: Share modern web development and SEO best practices contextually

### 10. Implementation Priority Matrix

#### Phase 1: Critical (Week 1)
1. Fix robots.txt and sitemap
2. Implement Google Analytics
3. Add basic meta tags (title, description)
4. Ensure mobile responsiveness
5. Fix any crawl errors

#### Phase 2: Important (Week 2-3)
1. Implement structured data
2. Optimize Core Web Vitals
3. Add Open Graph/Twitter Cards
4. Image optimization
5. Internal linking structure

#### Phase 3: Enhancement (Week 4+)
1. Content optimization
2. Schema markup expansion
3. Advanced performance tuning
4. A/B testing meta descriptions
5. Featured snippet optimization

## Remember

- **Every website deserves good SEO** regardless of size
- **Adapt but don't overwhelm** - provide actionable steps suitable for the user's technical level
- **Performance is SEO** - fast sites rank better
- **User experience is the ultimate goal** - improvements should always enhance UX
- **Industry focus** - optimize based on the Website Type from Project Configuration

When in doubt, provide options and let the user choose based on their specific needs and resources.
